47 SECTION 2.
48 Article 19A of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
49 American history recognition and significant documents, is amended by revising
50 subsection (a) of Code Section 20-2-1021, relating to display of historically significant
51 documents, as follows:
52 "(a) To increase student understanding of, and familiarity with, American historical
53 documents, public schools may display historically important excerpts from, or copies of,
54 those documents in school classrooms and common areas as appropriate. Local boards of
55 education and charter schools are strongly encouraged to allow and may encourage any
56 public school teacher or administrator to read or post in a public school building,
57 classroom, or event excerpts or portions of writings, documents, records, or images that
58 reflect the history of the United States, including, but not limited to:
59 (1) The Preamble to the Georgia Constitution;
60 (2) The Declaration of Independence;
61 (3) The United States Constitution, with emphasis on the 13th, 14th, and 15th
62 Amendments;
63 (4) The Bill of Rights;
64 (5) The Mayflower Compact;
65 (6) The national motto;
66 (7) The Pledge of Allegiance to the United States flag;
67 (7.1)(8) The Pledge of Allegiance to the Georgia flag;
68 (8)(9) The National Anthem;
