78 SECTION 3.
79 Said article is further amended by redesignating subsection (b) of Code Section 20-2-1021,
80 relating to display of historically significant documents, as subsection (c) and by adding a
81 new subsection to read as follows:
82 "(b)(1) No later than July 1, 2025, each public elementary and secondary school in this
83 state shall display in each of the three locations provided for in paragraph (2) of this
84 subsection a durable poster or framed copy of the Ten Commandments that meets the
85 requirements of paragraph (3) of this subsection.
86 (2) A poster or framed copy of the Ten Commandments, as required in paragraph (1) of
87 this subsection shall be displayed in a manner and location in which it can easily be read
88 by both students and adults in locations within each school facility fitting the following
89 descriptions:
90 (A) The main entrance of the main building;
91 (B) The main entrance of the school library or media center; and
92 (C) The main entrance of the cafeteria.
93 (3) Each poster or framed copy of the Ten Commandments, as required in paragraph (1)
94 of this subsection, shall:
